Model definition file created.
If loading via Setup.m does not work, try to solve issues by adapting the def files by hand.
The following issues might occur:
 - In SBML, compartements are often used as a kind of annotation and not for considering volume factors. Then compartement (should) have the same volumes. In D2D, a reaction of compounds located in different compartements might cause an error.
 - Non-standard function, e.g. something like "stepfunction()", which are not available in C have to be replaced or implemented properly.
 - The time axis (termed "PREDICTOR") might not assigned properly. Replace the respective variables properly.
